TASKS2.2:RESEARCH METHODOLOGY.
1. Stakeholder Interviews
•	Purpose: Gather in-depth qualitative insights.
•	Who: School administrators, teachers, IT staff, parent representatives.
•	Focus Areas:
o	Current communication challenges
o	Desired features (fee payment, performance tracking, event updates)
o	Concerns about usability and security
2. Surveys & Questionnaires
•	Purpose: Collect broad, quantifiable data.
•	Who: Students, parents, teachers.
•	Focus Areas:
o	Preferred communication channels
o	Frequency of updates needed
o	Ease of online payments
o	Satisfaction with current systems
3. Observation
•	Purpose: Understand how existing processes work in practice.
•	Method: Shadow staff during fee collection, event communication, and performance reporting.
•	Outcome: Identify inefficiencies and bottlenecks that the platform should solve.
4. Document Analysis
•	Purpose: Review existing policies, communication records, and IT infrastructure.
•	Outcome: Ensure the new system aligns with school regulations and integrates with current tools.
5. Focus Groups
•	Purpose: Encourage discussion and idea-sharing.
•	Who: Small groups of parents, students, and teachers.
•	Outcome: Prioritize features based on collective feedback and consensus.
6. Benchmarking / Competitor Analysis
•	Purpose: Study similar platforms used by other schools.
•	Outcome: Identify best practices and innovative features to adopt.
🎯 How to Use These Methods
1.	Start with interviews to capture strategic needs.
2.	Deploy surveys to validate and quantify those needs.
3.	Observe and analyze documents to uncover hidden inefficiencies.
4.	Run focus groups to refine priorities.
5.	Benchmark externally to ensure competitiveness.










