o	Real-time monitoring via IoT sensors.
o	Automated alerts for abnormal consumption.
2.	Upgrade Infrastructure:
o	Replace inefficient lighting with LED.
o	Modernize HVAC systems with smart controls.
3.	Integrate Renewables:
o	Solar panels for daytime operations.
o	Explore energy storage solutions for peak demand.
4.	Data-Driven Decision Making:
o	Develop dashboards for management.
o	Use predictive analytics to forecast energy needs.
5.	Employee Engagement:
o	Training programs on energy-saving practices.
o	Incentives for departments achieving efficiency targets.
