TASK 2.5 : REPORT FINDINGS.
Report Findings
1. Patient Data Security
•	Current Gaps Identified:
o	Inconsistent encryption standards across modules.
o	Limited role-based access control, leading to potential unauthorized access.
o	Manual backup processes increase risk of data loss.
•	Stakeholder Concerns:
o	Patients worry about privacy breaches and misuse of sensitive health data.
o	Administrators emphasize compliance with HIPAA/GDPR regulations.
•	Recommendations:
o	Implement end-to-end encryption for all patient records.
o	Strengthen authentication (multi-factor login).
o	Automate secure backups and disaster recovery protocols.
o	Introduce audit trails to monitor access and changes.
2. User Interface Preferences
•	Patient Feedback:
o	Desire for a simple, intuitive dashboard showing appointments, prescriptions, and test results.
o	Preference for mobile-friendly design with clear navigation.
o	Request for personalized notifications (appointment reminders, lab results).
•	Healthcare Staff Feedback:
o	Need for streamlined workflows (fewer clicks to access patient records).
o	Customizable views for doctors, nurses, and admin staff.
o	Integration with existing scheduling and billing systems.
•	Recommendations:
o	Design a clean, minimal UI with role-specific dashboards.
o	Ensure responsive design for mobile and tablet use.
o	Add color-coded alerts for urgent tasks (e.g., critical lab results).
o	Provide accessibility features (large fonts, screen reader compatibility).
3. Overall Insights
•	Security and usability are equally critical — patients demand trust, while staff need efficiency.
•	A balance between robust compliance measures and user-friendly design will drive adoption.
•	Prioritizing mobile access and personalized communication will enhance patient engagement.





