TASK 3.2: CREATION OF USER STORY

User Stories
1. Patient Perspective
•	As a patient, I want to book a virtual consultation with a doctor through the app,
•	So that I can receive medical advice without traveling to the healthcare facility.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Patients can view available doctors and time slots.
o	Patients can confirm appointments and receive reminders.
o	Patients can securely share medical history before the consultation.
o	Patients can join the video call with one click.
2. Doctor Perspective
•	As a doctor, I want to access patient records and conduct secure video consultations,
•	So that I can provide accurate medical advice remotely.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Doctors can view patient history and uploaded documents.
o	Doctors can prescribe medications digitally.
o	Doctors can update consultation notes in real time.
o	Doctors can manage their availability schedule.
3. Administrative Staff Perspective
•	As an administrator, I want to manage appointments and monitor system usage,
•	So that I can ensure smooth operations and optimize resource allocation.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Admins can approve or reschedule appointments.
o	Admins can generate reports on consultation frequency.
o	Admins can manage doctor availability and patient accounts.
o	Admins can monitor system performance and security logs.
